<item>
            <title>[SPR-2678] AbstractTransactionalSpringContextTests.onTearDownAfterTransaction() is not called if  endTransaction() is called in the test method</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2678</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In 2.0M3 and previous releases, onTearDownInTransaction() and onTearDownAfterTransaction() were being invoked regardless of whether endTransaction() was eagerly called from a test method. Since 2.0RC3 neither method is being invoked which is causing failures in my tests as my custom testDown method is not being called. &lt;br/&gt;
Shouldn&apos;t onTearDownAfterTransaction() always be invoked by AbstractTransactionalSpringContextTests regardless of the transaction status?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
            <key id="15127">SPR-2678</key>
            <summary>AbstractTransactionalSpringContextTests.onTearDownAfterTransaction() is not called if  endTransaction() is called in the test method</summary>
